FAQs
Is a degree from the USA recognized internationally?
Yes, degrees from American universities are recognized and respected worldwide, enhancing your career prospects globally.

What is the cost of studying in the USA?

Tuition fees range from $20,000 to $50,000 per year, with living expenses varying based on location and lifestyle.

Are there scholarships available for international students in the USA?

Yes, numerous scholarships are available from universities, the U.S. government, and private organizations based on academic merit and financial need.

How can Qadri International assist with study in USA?

Qadri International offers comprehensive support, including university selection, application assistance, and visa guidance to ensure a successful study abroad experience.

What is the OPT program in the USA?
The Optional Practical Training (OPT) program allows international students to work in the USA for up to one year (and up to three years for STEM graduates) after completing their studies.
